HEADWORD: Gruel
<hw>Gru"el</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF. <ets>gruel</ets>,
F. <ets>gruau</ets>; of German origin; cf. OHG. <ets>gruzzi</ets>
groats, G. <ets>gr⟦uum⟧tze</ets>, As. <ets>gr⟦umac⟧t</ets>. See
<er>Grout</er>.]</ety> <def>A light, liquid food, made by boiling meal
of maize, oatmeal, or flour in water or milk; thin porridge.</def>⟦br⟧
